        <svcproc svcproctype="tsireplace" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <para>Refer to the parts list for item numbers in parentheses.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Block front wheels of the vehicle.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support the rear of the vehicle with jack stands and remove rear axle from vehicle.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>A jack must never be used alone to support the vehicle while under-chassis service is
                            being performed. The jack may lower and serious personal injury could result. Always support
                            vehicle with floor stands.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove rear suspension rear "dog bone" crossmember.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a reinforcement (2) on each frame rail as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9503011">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    with the bolts and nuts removed with the "dog bone" crossmember.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9503011" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g9503011" filename="../tsifigures/G9503011.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use the reinforcement as a template to drill four 21/32 inch outer holes (two on each
                    end of the reinforcements) as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9503011">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install 5/8 Inch-18 x 1-3/4 Inch hex flg hd bolts (9) and 5/8 Inch-18 hex flg lock nuts
                    (10) in the drilled holes. Tighten all fasteners in the reinforcement to 200-240 ft-lbs. (271-325
                    Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the crossmembers (1) back to back to the side rail reinforcements as illustrated
                    in Figure 1, with 1/2 Inch-20 x 1-1/4 Inch hex flg hd bolts (11) and 1/2 Inch-20 hex flg lock nuts
                    (12). Tighten to 200-240 ft-lbs. (271-325 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Weld the torque rod bracket (7) and axle housing reinforcement plates (8) to the axle
                    housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9503012">Figure 2</hotlnk>). Refer to TSI-94-14-03, dated October 1994, for the
                    procedure to weld the torque rod bracket and plates to the axle housing.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9503012" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic id="g9503012" filename="../tsifigures/G9503012.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Invisible ultraviolet and infrared rays emitted in welding can injure unprotected eyes and
                            skin. Protection such as welder's helmet with dark colored filter lenses of the proper
                            density must be used. GTAW or TIG welding will produce intense radiation, therefore, filter
                            plate lenses of the deepest shade providing adequate visibility are recommended. It is
                            strongly recommended that persons working in the weld area wear flash safety goggles. Also
                            wear protective clothing.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install rear axle.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the torque rod bracket (4), torque rod reinforcement plate (3) and the shorter
                    half of the torque rod to the crossmember as illustrated in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9503011">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                    with 5/8 Inch-18 x 5-1/2 Inch hex flg hd bolts (13) and 5/8 Inch-18 hex flg lock nuts (10). Snug the
                    fasteners.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The long half of the torque rod will only slide into the shorter half 3 inches. It may be
                        necessary to cut off the longer half to get the correct length between the rear axle torque rod
                        bracket and the bracket on the rear crossmember.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fasten longer half of the torque rod to the axle housing torque rod bracket with 5/8
                    Inch-18 x 3-3/4 Inch hex flg hd bolts (14) and 5/8 Inch-18 hex flg lock nuts (10). Snug the
                    fasteners.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tack weld the torque rod halves together. Remove the torque rod and finish weld the
                    halves together.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the torque rod. Tighten the fasteners on each end of the torque rod to 200-240
                    ft-lbs. (271-325 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
